@startuml
!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center

title Retweet Leaderboard - Control Flow

actor "Twitter User" as User
participant "Twitter Event Source\n(aws-serverless-twitter-event-source)" as TwitterSource
participant "TweetProcessorHandler\n(Lambda)" as TweetHandler
participant "TweetProcessor" as Processor
participant "Tweet" as TweetParser
participant "RetweetCountComparator" as Comparator
participant "Leaderboard" as LeaderboardLogic
participant "DynamoDB\n(Leaderboard Table)" as DynamoDB
participant "API Gateway" as APIGateway
participant "GetLeaderboardHandler\n(Lambda)" as GetHandler
participant "Web Browser\n(UI)" as Browser

== Tweet Processing Flow ==

User -> TwitterSource: Post/Retweet
activate TwitterSource
TwitterSource -> TweetHandler: Trigger with tweet JSON
activate TweetHandler

TweetHandler -> Processor: handleRequest(tweetJson)
activate Processor

Processor -> TweetParser: fromJson(tweetJson)
activate TweetParser
TweetParser -> TweetParser: Parse JSON\nExtract username,\nretweetCount, favoriteCount
TweetParser --> Processor: Tweet object
deactivate TweetParser

Processor -> Processor: Filter:\n- Exclude native retweets\n- Require retweetCount >= 1

alt Valid Tweet
    Processor -> Processor: Convert to RetweetCount object

    Processor -> LeaderboardLogic: update(username, retweetCount)
    activate LeaderboardLogic

    LeaderboardLogic -> DynamoDB: Load current LeaderboardRecord
    activate DynamoDB
    DynamoDB --> LeaderboardLogic: LeaderboardRecord with retweetCounts map
    deactivate DynamoDB

    LeaderboardLogic -> LeaderboardLogic: Update retweetCounts map\nfor username

    LeaderboardLogic -> Comparator: sort(retweetCounts)
    activate Comparator
    Comparator -> Comparator: Sort by retweetCount DESC,\nthen favoriteCount DESC
    Comparator --> LeaderboardLogic: Sorted retweetCounts
    deactivate Comparator

    LeaderboardLogic -> DynamoDB: Save updated LeaderboardRecord
    activate DynamoDB
    DynamoDB --> LeaderboardLogic: Success
    deactivate DynamoDB

    LeaderboardLogic --> Processor: Update complete
    deactivate LeaderboardLogic

    Processor --> TweetHandler: Success
else Invalid Tweet
    Processor --> TweetHandler: Filtered out
end

deactivate Processor
TweetHandler --> TwitterSource: Processing complete
deactivate TweetHandler
deactivate TwitterSource

== Leaderboard Retrieval Flow ==

Browser -> APIGateway: GET /leaderboard?limit=N
activate Browser
activate APIGateway

APIGateway -> GetHandler: Invoke with query params
activate GetHandler

GetHandler -> LeaderboardLogic: getLeaderboard(limit)
activate LeaderboardLogic

LeaderboardLogic -> DynamoDB: Load LeaderboardRecord
activate DynamoDB
DynamoDB --> LeaderboardLogic: LeaderboardRecord with retweetCounts map
deactivate DynamoDB

LeaderboardLogic -> LeaderboardLogic: Convert retweetCounts map\nusing RetweetCountsMapConverter

LeaderboardLogic -> Comparator: sort(retweetCounts)
activate Comparator
Comparator -> Comparator: Sort by retweetCount DESC,\nthen favoriteCount DESC
Comparator --> LeaderboardLogic: Sorted retweetCounts
deactivate Comparator

LeaderboardLogic -> LeaderboardLogic: Apply limit (if specified)

LeaderboardLogic --> GetHandler: List of RetweetCount objects
deactivate LeaderboardLogic

GetHandler -> GetHandler: Convert to JSON response

GetHandler --> APIGateway: JSON response with leaderboard data
deactivate GetHandler

APIGateway --> Browser: HTTP 200 with JSON
deactivate APIGateway

Browser -> Browser: Display leaderboard in HTML
deactivate Browser

@enduml
